      %h1 Features
      .row
        .span3
          .thumbnail
            %img{:alt => "", :src => "http://placehold.it/260x180"}
              .caption
                %h5 Native File Management
                %p Nimbus mounts your CloudApp files as a drive you can open in Finder. Open, rename, delete, add, and Quicklook your uploaded files!
                
        .span3
          .thumbnail
            %img{:alt => "", :src => "http://placehold.it/260x180"}
              .caption
                %h5 Fast Access
                %p Nimbus downloads only the files it needs to, saving you bandwidth and time. It also caches frequently used files for speedy access.
        
        .span3
          .thumbnail
            %img{:alt => "", :src => "http://placehold.it/260x180"}
              .caption
                %h5 Painless Install
                %p Simply download and install. OSXFuse will be installed if you do not already have it.
          
        .span3
          .thumbnail
            %img{:alt => "", :src => "http://placehold.it/260x180"}
              .caption
                %h5 Sortable
                %p Nimbus creates virtual folders that allow you to view your files by category: Popular, Images, Text, Audio, Video, etc.
      
      .row
        .span6
          %h1 How does it work?
          %p Nimbus sits between the CloudApp API and OSXFUSE API, translating Finder actions into CloudApp requests.

